8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 496, L.D. 1207, “An Act to Require the
10 Department of Environmental Protection to Monitor Air and Water Temperatures Around
11 Commercial Solar Energy Developments”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Amend the Site Location of Development Laws to Require a 100-foot
14 Buffer Between Solar Energy Developments and Rivers, Streams and Brooks'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §484, sub-§11 is enacted to read:
18 11. Special provision; solar energy development. In the case of a proposed solar
19 energy development, the development will not be constructed within 100 feet of a river,
20 stream or brook. This subsection does not apply to vegetation removal activities necessary
21 for shade management or road or utility line crossings within 100 feet of a river, stream or
22 brook.
23 As used in this subsection, "solar energy development" means a development that uses a
24 solar energy system consisting of ground-mounted solar panels to convert solar energy to
25 electrical energy and includes generating facilities and associated facilities.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment changes the title of and replaces the bill. It amends the site location
3300 of development laws to provide that a proposed solar energy development may not be
3311 constructed within 100 feet of a river, stream or brook. That provision does not apply to
